{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491007","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491007"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:27:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:27:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"800"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"800","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/800"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.66,0.16,0,0.11,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"800"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86462"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"800","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/800"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"800"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70742"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"2082"},{"type":"tags","id":"4632"},{"type":"tags","id":"5601"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12922"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"831"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1001"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86462","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/86462"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 78-year-old man presents to the Pre-admission Clinic for assessment prior to an elective inguinal hernia repair. He has a history of motion sickness when travelling by car or boat. His medical history includes hypertension and osteoarthritis. His medications include amlodipine and paracetamol. He is a current smoker with a 30 pack-year history.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Total intravenous anaesthesia with propofol is planned for this procedure.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following factors most increases the risk of post-operative nausea and vomiting?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["History of motion sickness","Intravenous propofol anaesthesia","Male gender","Current smoking status","Age over 75 years"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPost-operative nausea and vomiting (PONV) is a common and distressing complication affecting approximately 30% of patients following general anaesthesia. Risk assessment using validated tools helps identify patients who may benefit from prophylactic antiemetics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHistory of motion sickness\u003C/strong\u003E is one of the four major Apfel risk factors for PONV, along with female gender, non-smoking status, and post-operative opioid use. A history of motion sickness or previous PONV significantly increases the risk of PONV in the current episode.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous propofol anaesthesia\u003C/strong\u003E actually reduces the risk of PONV compared to volatile anaesthetic agents. Total intravenous anaesthesia (TIVA) with propofol is often chosen specifically for patients at high risk of PONV.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMale gender\u003C/strong\u003E is protective against PONV. Female gender is one of the major Apfel risk factors, with females having approximately three times the risk of males.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECurrent smoking status\u003C/strong\u003E is also protective against PONV. Being a non-smoker is one of the major Apfel risk factors, though the mechanism for this association is not fully understood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAge over 75 years\u003C/strong\u003E has minimal impact on PONV risk. Younger age (less than 50 years) is associated with a slightly increased risk of PONV, but age is not one of the major risk factors.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["History of motion sickness is one of the four major Apfel risk factors for post-operative nausea and vomiting.","Total intravenous anaesthesia with propofol reduces the risk of post-operative nausea and vomiting compared to volatile agents.","Female gender, non-smoking status, and post-operative opioid use are the other major Apfel risk factors."],"references":["Apfel CC, Philip BK, Cakmakkaya OS, Shilling A, Shi YY, Leslie JB, et al. Who is at risk for postdischarge nausea and vomiting after ambulatory surgery? Anesthesiology. 2012;117(3):475-86.","Apfel CC, Heidrich FM, Jukar-Rao S, Jalota L, Hornuss C, Whelan RP, et al. Evidence-based analysis of risk factors for postoperative nausea and vomiting. Br J Anaesth. 2012;109(5):742-53."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70742"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"800"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/70742"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-21T22:22:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-21T22:24:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"800"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86462"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"d